==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Depletion
<hw>De*ple"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧pl⟦eacute⟧tion</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
depleting or emptying.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>the act or process of diminishing
the quantity of fluid in the vessels by bloodletting or otherwise; also
excessive evacuation, as in severe diarrhea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Depletive</ent>⟦br⟧
